"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771627","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-10-23","<p>No estimate has been made of this as it is not possible to know how many people above state pension age would be affected from 1 April 2019.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2017-10-23T14:27:12.567Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771627/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771627/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771627/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-10-16","Pensioners: Housing Benefits","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what estimate he has made of how many people above state pension age will no longer have their full rent covered by support for housing costs from 1 April 2019.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","107995"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771628","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-10-19","<p>The Independent Case Examiner’s Office has not been assigned a budget to deal with the complaints from woman affected by the increase in state pension age.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2017-10-19T12:02:39.487Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771628/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771628/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771628/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-10-16","State Retirement Pensions: Females","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what budget has been assigned to the dedicated team to address complaints by women adversely affected by an increase in the state pension age.","false","Biography information for David Linden","Glasgow East","David Linden","108023"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771629","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-10-19","<p>The Independent Case Examiner’s Office has a dedicated team of three full time equivalent staff investigating complaints from women affected by the increase in state pension age.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2017-10-19T12:10:57.243Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771629/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771629/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771629/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-10-16","State Retirement Pensions: Females","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many full-time equivalent staff work in the dedicated team to address complaints by women adversely affected by an increase in the state pension age.","false","Biography information for David Linden","Glasgow East","David Linden","108024"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771630","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-10-25","<p>The number of young unemployed claimants is continuing to fall. The proportion of young people (aged 16-24) who are unemployed and not in full time education is at a new record low of 4.8% and the youth claimant count in Angus has fallen by 40% since 2010.</p><p> </p><p>As planned, we have also introduced the Youth Obligation to provide intensive support for 18-21 year olds making a new claim to Universal Credit full service from April 2017. We are rolling out the Youth Obligation in line with the roll-out schedule for Universal Credit full service across Scotland, therefore, young claimants in Angus will start receiving more intensive support from the Youth Obligation from November 2017.</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2017-10-25T10:44:39.017Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771630/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771630/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771630/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-10-16","Unemployment: Angus","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what plans the Government has to tackle youth unemployment in Angus constituency.","false","Biography information for Kirstene Hair","Angus","Kirstene Hair","107808"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771631","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-10-23","<p>Jobcentre staff are in contact with BAE Systems and stand ready to offer support once the consultation period ends and a decision on redundancies has been made.</p><p>Each of our Jobcentre Districts deploy resources to assist with Redundancy Support which varies according to the situation and the requirements of the workforce.</p><p>The Rapid Response Service is delivered in partnership with a range of national and local partners, including National Careers Service and local service providers. Working closely with BAE Systems we will agree and provide a tailored package which could include:</p><ul><li>matching to known local job vacancies;</li><li>helping to construct or improve their CV and enhance their job-search skills;</li><li>providing general information about benefits and how to make a claim;</li><li>identifying transferable skills and training needs;</li><li>providing job-focussed training to develop vocational skills in demand in the local labour market;</li><li>help to meet discretionary costs e.g.: travel to training course expenses</li><li>where there is scope to do so, support might be delivered on a group basis, for example by bringing redundant workers and employers together at a jobs fair.</li><li>Working with Talent Retention Solution (TRS) to bring together specialists whose jobs may be at risk with companies that are looking to recruit skilled staff</li></ul><p> </p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2017-10-23T15:12:33.47Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771631/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771631/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771631/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-10-16","BAE Systems: Redundancy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many staff are employed in his Department's Rapid Response Team set up to assist BAE Systems employees affected by recent job losses; in which regions those staff are based; and how many BAE Systems staff potentially affected by job losses have been contacted by a member of that Rapid Response team.","false","Biography information for Diana Johnson","Kingston upon Hull North","Diana Johnson","107786"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771632","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-10-20","<p>The Child Maintenance Service already has the power to oblige employers to comply with deduction from earnings orders and supports employers through provision of an online self-service portal and dedicated Employer Payment Team.</p><p> </p><p>Employers who fail to comply with a deduction from earnings order are contacted as soon as possible to establish the reasons for non-compliance and secure payment of the outstanding amounts due. If compliance action is required we can use our criminal powers to enforce the maximum penalty of a fine. We have no plans to introduce additional powers.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2017-10-20T13:28:22.49Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771632/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771632/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771632/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-10-16","Children: Maintenance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, if he will bring forward proposals for additional powers of enforcement to ensure that employers comply with deductions of earnings issued by the Child Maintenance Service.","false","Biography information for Grahame Morris","Easington","Grahame Morris","107897"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771633","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-10-20","<p>The Child Maintenance Service (CMS) has made significant improvements to better the working relationships between themselves and employers in order to process Deduction from Earnings Orders (DEO) in a timely manner.</p><p> </p><p>Previously all Deduction from Earnings Orders (DEO) were handled by individual caseworkers. In order to improve DEO compliance a dedicated team have been established in CMS who work closely with employers, providing support and advice throughout the process to ensure that payments are processed in a timely manner.</p><p> </p><p>The team has implemented a process from tracking and escalating issues where a DEO payment may not have been made or where the employer has not fully met their DEO requirements.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2017-10-20T13:34:07.107Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771633/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771633/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771633/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-10-16","Children: Maintenance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment he has made of levels of co-operation between employers and the Child Maintenance Service to process deductions of earnings in a timely manner.","false","Biography information for Grahame Morris","Easington","Grahame Morris","107859"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771634","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-10-23","<p>The Department for Work and Pensions (DWP) uses a virtual telephone network which will route the call to the most appropriate agent available with required skills to support the caller. As a result we are not able to issue direct contact numbers for benefit centres.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>DWP telephone numbers are signposted to customers for the services that they wish to access and this signposting will be refreshed as the recently announced move to Freephone numbers progresses.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2017-10-23T14:59:21.427Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771634/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771634/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771634/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-10-16","Department for Work and Pensions: Telephone Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, if he will provide hon. Members with a direct telephone contact number for benefit centres in their and neighbouring constituencies.","false","Biography information for Grahame Morris","Easington","Grahame Morris","107881"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771635","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-10-23","<p>We are committed to ensuring that the WCA assesses people fairly and accurately, which is why we keep our processes under review. Since ESA was introduced, we have made a number of changes to strengthen the assessment process for people with mental health conditions. We took forward a number of recommendations from Professor Harrington and Dr Litchfield who independently reviewed the WCA, including redesigning the ESA50 claimant questionnaire to make it clear that evidence from healthcare professionals and advocates is particularly valuable in mental health cases.</p><p>More information regarding these independent reviews can be found at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/work-capability-assessment-independent-review-year-1" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/work-capability-assessment-independent-review-year-1</a></p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2017-10-23T15:56:12.297Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771635/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771635/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771635/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-10-16","Employment and Support Allowance: Mental Illness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, if he will review the employment and support allowance assessment criteria to tackle the difficulties faced by applicants suffering with mental health problems including anxiety and depression.","false","Biography information for Thangam Debbonaire","Bristol West","Thangam Debbonaire","107866"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771636","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-10-23","<p>The table below gives details of the total number of Departmental sites in Wales along with the full time equivalent staff numbers for the period for which we maintain records.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>This includes Contact Centres, Debt Centres, Pensions Centres and Benefit Centres.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>It is not possible to strip out the numbers of buildings or staff solely involved in JCP front of house duties.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><br><p>Year</p><p> </p></td><td><br><p>No of Sites</p><p> </p></td><td><br><p>FTE</p><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><br><p>2017</p><p> </p></td><td><br><p>75</p><p> </p></td><td><br><p>3994</p><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><br><p>2016</p><p> </p></td><td><br><p>75</p><p> </p></td><td><br><p>3816</p><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><br><p>2015</p><p> </p></td><td><br><p>77</p><p> </p></td><td><br><p>3363</p><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><br><p>2014</p><p> </p></td><td><br><p>78</p><p> </p></td><td><br><p>3087</p><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><br><p>2013</p><p> </p></td><td><br><p>77</p><p> </p></td><td><br><p>3184</p><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><br><p>2012</p><p> </p></td><td><br><p>76</p><p> </p></td><td><br><p>3288</p><p> </p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2017-10-23T14:21:31.357Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771636/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771636/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771636/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-10-16","Jobcentres: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what the number of (a) job centres and (b) full-time permanent job centre employees there were in Wales in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Jo Stevens","Cardiff Central","Jo Stevens","108083"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771637","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-10-23","<p>As at 31<sup>st</sup> July 2017 the number of full-time equivalent staff currently employed at Easterhouse jobcentre in Glasgow is 17.14.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2017-10-23T15:49:36.997Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771637/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771637/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771637/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-10-16","Jobcentres: Glasgow","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many full-time equivalent staff are currently employed at Easterhouse jobcentre in Glasgow.","false","Biography information for David Linden","Glasgow East","David Linden","108056"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771638","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-10-23","<p>The Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy has not estimated the cost of extending employee rights to parental leave to self-employed fathers.</p><p> </p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2017-10-23T14:06:49.653Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771638/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771638/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771638/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-10-16","Self-employed: Parental Leave","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what recent estimate he has made of the cost of removing the parental support inequality that exists for self-employed fathers who wish to take parental leave to care for a new-born child.","false","Biography information for Dr David Drew","Stroud","Dr David Drew","107784"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771639","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-10-19","<p>The Government is assessing and will respond appropriately in due course.</p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2017-10-19T14:47:52.563Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771639/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771639/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771639/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-10-16","Fracking: Ryedale","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, whether he has made an assessment that (a) the relevant criteria for hydraulic fracturing consent have been met for the KM8 wellsite in Ryedale, North Yorkshire and (b) it is appropriate to grant hydraulic fracturing consent; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Rebecca Long Bailey","Salford and Eccles","Rebecca Long Bailey","107816"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771641","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-10-24","<p>Sector Deals are an open challenge to industry to come to Government with proposals to transform and upgrade productivity, earning power and investment in their sector. We are prepared to work with any sector which can organise behind strong leadership to address shared challenges and opportunities. Sector deals are open to both established and emerging industries, and to sectors of all sizes. The Government will respond positively to compelling propositions if they can demonstrate how specific actions from Government and from businesses will improve the competitiveness of the sector in question.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2017-10-24T11:29:09.227Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771641/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771641/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771641/answer","Devizes","Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771641/answer/previousversion/16337","Biography information for Claire Perry","201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-10-16","Industry","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what criteria the Government used to decide (a) how much should be allocated to different sectors through the industrial strategy and (b) which sectors should be granted a sector deal.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","107984"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771642","HM Treasury","false","2017-10-19","<p>The Government laid the Payment Services Regulations on 19 July 2017, which supports bank customers to take greater control over their data.</p><p> </p><p>The Government is also working with the Open Banking Implementation Entity to implement the CMA Retail Banking Market Investigation Order. The order facilitates the introduction of a range of Open Banking services for bank customers from 2018. Open Banking allows customers to exercise control over their data in a way that is secure, safe and standardised.</p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay",,"2017-10-19T16:04:01.713Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771642/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771642/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771642/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-10-16","Bank Services","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what steps the Government is taking to allow (a) bank customers and (b) customers of open banking services greater control over their banking data.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","107985"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771643","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-10-24","<p>Government has supported and invested in the creation of a network of 38 Growth Hubs (one in each Local Enterprise Partnership area), providing businesses across England with tailored advice and support. Growth Hubs simplify the business support landscape by bringing together all of the organisations involved in the provision of business support (including those delivered by local councils) and provide a local ‘single point of contact.’ Whilst Growth Hubs aim to improve awareness, coordination and take-up of local and national business support, it is local and combined authorities who are responsible for evaluating these programmes and reporting on outcomes to funders. However, the Honourable Member might like to note that we are funding the What Works Centre for Local Economic Growth and the Enterprise Research Centre to improve the quality of local evaluations and to investigate impacts of business support at a national level. Of the 23 high quality evaluations reviewed so far, 17 found positive programme impacts on at least one business outcome</p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2017-10-24T11:26:52.553Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771643/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771643/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771643/answer","Devizes","Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771643/answer/previousversion/16338","Biography information for Claire Perry","201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-10-16","Business: Local Government","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what assessment he has made of the effect on productivity of local council business support programmes.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","107986"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771644","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-10-19","<p>The Government is committed to supporting the construction sector to increase the gender and ethnic diversity of its workforce, to ensure there are opportunities for all who wish to pursue construction careers, regardless of their background. The Construction Industry Training Board (CITB) has developed a ‘Be Fair’ framework, which includes freely available fairness and inclusion training modules for construction firms.</p><p>In addition, CITB’s careers hub, ‘Go Construct’, provides online guidance and case studies for prospective employees - and employers - on a range of diversity topics, including gender and race. We are engaged in discussions with the sector as to how further improvements in its diversity can best be achieved.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2017-10-19T16:23:37.633Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771644/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771644/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771644/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-10-16","Construction: Equality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what steps the Government is taking to promote (a) gender and (b) racial diversity in the construction industry.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","107987"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771645","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-10-23","<p>For the 12 month period up to end of March 2017, the Start-up Loans Company granted 28 loans totalling over £333,500 to businesses in Bolton.</p><p> </p><p>For the same period, 11 loans were granted totalling over £114,750 to businesses in Bolton West.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2017-10-23T14:08:40.553Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771645/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771645/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771645/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-10-16","New Businesses: Bolton","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what the (a) number and (b) financial value of start-up loans was for small businesses in (i) Bolton and (ii) Bolton West constituency in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Chris Green","Bolton West","Chris Green","108078"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771646","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-10-23","<p>We are working hard to support businesses and entrepreneurs across the UK to ensure they can access the finance and wider support to grow and have the right conditions for companies to invest long-term.</p><p> </p><p>At Budget 2016 we announced reductions in business rates worth almost £9 billion over the next 5 years, included permanently doubling Small Business Rate Relief and extending the thresholds of the relief ensuring the smallest businesses pay no rates at all.</p><p><em> </em></p><p>For the 12 month period up to end of March 2017, BBB programmes have facilitated over <strong>£6.17m</strong> of finance to <strong>76</strong> businesses in Bolton. Within this, the Start-up Loans Company granted <strong>28</strong> loans totalling over <strong>£330k.</strong></p><p><em> </em></p><p> </p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2017-10-23T13:47:32.29Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771646/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771646/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771646/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-10-16","New Businesses: Bolton","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what financial support his Department provides to (a) small and (b) start-up businesses in Bolton.","false","Biography information for Chris Green","Bolton West","Chris Green","108079"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771647","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-10-23","<p>This Government has set out its vision to meet R&amp;D investment of 2.4% of GDP within ten years and 3% in the longer-term. We have already increased research and development investment by £4.7 billion over the period 2017-18 to 2020-21. This equates to an extra £2 billion per year by 2020-21 and is an increase of around 20% to total government R&amp;D spending, more than any increase in any parliament since 1979.</p><p> </p><p>We will support business to do more R&amp;D and innovation through our industrial strategy by making sure the wider business environment supports R&amp;D investment and ensuring businesses have access to the skilled people they need to do R&amp;D.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2017-10-23T14:18:00.96Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771647/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771647/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771647/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-10-16","Science: Investment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what progress has been made on creating a roadmap for increasing investment in science to three per cent of gross domestic product in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Chris Green","Bolton West","Chris Green","108080"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771648","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-10-23","<p>If a consumer with a first generation (SMETS1) smart meter switches to an energy supplier who is not able to maintain their smart service on switching, the consumer will not face any additional costs.</p><p> </p><p>Work is currently underway to bring SMETS1 meters into the national communications network, so that consumers can keep their smart services when they switch supplier.</p><p> </p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2017-10-23T14:10:49.737Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771648/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771648/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771648/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-10-16","Energy: Meters","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what discussions he has had with energy suppliers on ensuring that consumers who have smart meters installed are not faced with additional costs when changing supplier.","false","Biography information for Kate Green","Stretford and Urmston","Kate Green","108076"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771649","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-10-24","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I have given today to Question UIN 107951.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry","107948","2017-10-24T16:48:22.31Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771649/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771649/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771649/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-10-16","Vauxhall Motors: Working Hours","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, which members of PSA senior management he has met since the announcement of the reduction in the number of shifts at the Vauxhall car plant at Ellesmere Port.","false","Biography information for Bill Esterson","Sefton Central","Bill Esterson","107949"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771650","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-10-24","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I have given today to Question UIN 107951.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry","107949","2017-10-24T16:48:22.247Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771650/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771650/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771650/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-10-16","Vauxhall Motors: Working Hours","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what recent discussions he has had with PSA on the reduction of the number of shifts at the Vauxhall car plant at Ellesmere Port.","false","Biography information for Bill Esterson","Sefton Central","Bill Esterson","107948"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771651","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-10-24","<p>The Department for Work and Pensions’ will provide advice and support to those affected and the Jobcentre Plus Rapid Response Service will help workers get back into employment as soon as possible. With many of the people working in the plant living in across the border in Wales, the Welsh Government also stands ready to support.</p><p>We will work with the company and Unite Union to consider how the Talent Retention Scheme can help ensure that workforce skills are not lost to the industry.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2017-10-24T12:08:18.637Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771651/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771651/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771651/answer","Devizes","Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771651/answer/previousversion/16327","Biography information for Claire Perry","201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-10-16","Vauxhall Motors: Redundancy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what plans he has to ensure jobs are available of equivalent skills for workers who lose their jobs at Vauxhall Ellesmere Port.","false","Biography information for Bill Esterson","Sefton Central","Bill Esterson","108082"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771652","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-10-24","<p>The company has said that the planned job reductions link to reduced vehicle sales and therefore production requirements. Exchange rate changes will affect individual companies such as Vauxhall in often complex ways. The Government has a range of policies in place to support the competitiveness of the UK business environment.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2017-10-24T12:07:57.787Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771652/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771652/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771652/answer","Devizes","Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771652/answer/previousversion/16317","Biography information for Claire Perry","201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-10-16","Vauxhall Motors: Exchange Rates","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what assessment he has made of the effect on manufacturing costs at Vauxhall Ellesmere Port of changes in the exchange rate since the referendum on the UK's membership of the EU.","false","Biography information for Bill Esterson","Sefton Central","Bill Esterson","107950"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771653","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-10-24","<p>I refer to the Statement that I made to this House on Monday 16 October, Official Report, column 600, about the developments at Vauxhall’s Ellesmere Port site. Ultimately this is a commercial decision taken by Vauxhall. My right hon. Friend the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, together with other Ministers and officials have had numerous conversations with the senior management of Vauxhall, its parent group PSA and as well as conversations with the local council, Local Enterprise Partnership management and the General Secretary of Unite on the day of the announcement.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2017-10-24T16:44:33.62Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771653/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771653/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771653/answer","Devizes","Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771653/answer/previousversion/16326","Biography information for Claire Perry","201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-10-16","Vauxhall Motors: Redundancy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what discussions he has had with (a) businesses and (b) representatives of the Vauxhall Ellesmere Port supply chain workforce on job losses at that plant.","false","Biography information for Bill Esterson","Sefton Central","Bill Esterson","107951"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771654","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-10-19","<p>The model clauses incorporated into the Licence are those deriving from Schedule 3 of The Petroleum (Production) Regulations 1966 as set out in Schedule 3 of the Petroleum (Current Model Clauses) Order 1999.</p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2017-10-19T16:24:27.85Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771654/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771654/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771654/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-10-16","Petroleum (Production) Regulations 1966","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what changes have been made to the Model Clauses incorporated in PL080 Licence from the Petroleum (Production) Regulations 1966.","false","Biography information for Rachael Maskell","York Central","Rachael Maskell","107959"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771655","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-10-19","<p>Licensing for marine disposal of sediments around the South Wales coastline is a devolved matter for Natural Resources Wales and the Welsh Government. Nuclear safety and environmental protection are of paramount importance to the UK Government. The UK has a strong regulatory system and companies involved in the civil nuclear industry are required to meet robust standards overseen by independent regulators.</p><p> </p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2017-10-19T13:41:29.023Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771655/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771655/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771655/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-10-16","Hinkley Point C Power Station: South Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, whether he has had discussions with the Welsh Government on minimising any potential effect of radioactive sediment from the Hinkley Point nuclear power plant on the South Wales coastline.","false","Biography information for Nick Thomas-Symonds","Torfaen","Nick Thomas-Symonds","107973"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771656","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-10-24","<p>Sector Deals are an open challenge to industry to come to Government with proposals to transform productivity, earning power and investment in their sector. We are prepared to work with any sector which can organise behind strong leadership to address shared challenges and opportunities. The business community is best placed to identify what firms really need. Government will be there to support them</p><p> </p><p>Since the launch of the Industrial Strategy consultation in January over sixty sectors have expressed interest in a Sector Deal, many of which are working up detailed proposals to submit to Government.</p><p> </p><p>Sectors should work with their sponsor Departments when developing proposals and can submit them directly to the Industrial Strategy Unit at BEIS at <a href="mailto:sectordeals@beis.gov.uk" target="_blank">sectordeals@beis.gov.uk</a>.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry","107971 ; 107972","2017-10-24T14:08:23.913Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771656/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771656/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771656/answer","Devizes","Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/771656/answer/previousversion/16333","Biography information for Claire Perry","201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-10-16","Industry","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, to whom businesses developing sector deals as part of the industrial strategy should submit their proposals.","false","Biography information for Peter Kyle","Hove","Peter Kyle","107970"
