"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/770074","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-10-18","<p>Mayoral remuneration will be a matter for Sheffield City Region to decide and to give consent to the secondary legislation necessary for any such remuneration to be paid.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry",,"2017-10-18T13:45:06.683Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/770074/answer","Biography information for Jake Berry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/770074/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/770074/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-10-13","Mayors: Sheffield","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what the salary of the proposed Sheffield City Region Mayor will be.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","107702"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/770075","Home Office","false","2017-10-18","<p>The Government expects to lay the Regulations provided for under section 136A of the Mental Health Act, shortly.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2017-10-18T14:56:20.677Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/770075/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/770075/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/770075/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-10-13","Police Custody: Mental Illness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what plans she has to introduce regulations on the use of police stations as a place of safety under section 136A of the Mental Health Act 1983.","false","Biography information for Mr Steve Reed","Croydon North","Mr Steve Reed","107716"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/770076","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-10-20","<p>The number of defendants proceeded against at magistrates’ courts for offences under the Gambling Act 2005 in England and Wales, in each year between 2012 and 2016, can be viewed in the attached table.</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch",,"2017-10-20T06:59:16.727Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/770076/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/770076/answer","Gambling Act 2005 detailed offences 2012-2016.pdf","Gambling Act 2005 detailed offences 2012-2016.pdf","Gambling Act 2005 offences 2012-2016","Gambling Act 2005 offences 2012-2016","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/770076/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2017-10-13","Gambling: Prosecutions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, how many prosecutions under the Gambling Act 2005 there have been in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Tom Watson","107704"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/770077","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-10-19","<p>There is a contractual mechanism for dealing with recommendations made in HM Inspectorate of Probation reports and, as a result, Community Rehabilitation Companies (CRCs) are required to prepare action plans to address the issues raised. Contract Management Teams give high priority to ensuring that those plans are followed through, and ensure that those actions are successful in addressing the points raised.</p><p> </p><p>Public protection is our top priority and we will take all necessary action to make sure the probation system is reducing reoffending and preventing future victims.</p><p> </p><p>We have fundamentally reformed probation so that for the first time ever all offenders given a custodial sentence receive probation support on release. We continue to work with the CRCs to ensure they deliver services that have the correct levels of supervision and support for offenders.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2017-10-19T11:56:11.683Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/770077/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/770077/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/770077/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-10-13","Probation: Gloucestershire","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what steps his Department plans to take to address the problems identified in HM Inspectorate of Probation's report on Gloucestershire with service delivery  carried out by working links.","false","Biography information for Kate Green","Stretford and Urmston","Kate Green","107725"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/770078","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-10-25","<p>(a) The latest figures are available in the Official Universal Credit Statistics at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/universal-credit-29-apr-2013-to-14-sep-2017" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/universal-credit-29-apr-2013-to-14-sep-2017</a></p><p> </p><p>(b) The information is not currently available</p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2017-10-25T10:50:12.857Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/770078/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/770078/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/770078/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-10-13","Universal Credit: Greater Manchester","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, (a) how many claimants are currently in receipt of universal credit and (b) what estimate he has made of the number of such claimants once the roll-out of universal credit has been completed in each of the 10 local authority areas in Greater Manchester.","false","Biography information for Jim McMahon","Oldham West and Royton","Jim McMahon","107688"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/770079","HM Treasury","false","2017-10-23","<p>HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) has five 0345 numbers, and their specific details can be found on the GOV.UK website. HMRC does not receive any revenue from these numbers.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2017-10-23T14:29:16.437Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/770079/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/770079/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/770079/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-10-13","Treasury: Telephone Services","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many 0345 telephone numbers are in use by his Department; and how much revenue has been generated by each such telephone number in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Jim McMahon","Oldham West and Royton","Jim McMahon","107737"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/770080","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-10-23","<p>The Department for Work and Pensions’ (DWP) currently has 297 0345 numbers in use and this includes Fax machines, textphone services and also the provision of services in line with legislative requirements.</p><p> </p><p>99% of the calls received by the Department are managed through 60 of the 0345 numbers available.</p><p> </p><p>DWP continually monitor activity on all its telephony platform and in the last 12 months have removed 214 0345 numbers from use, where it is safe to do so and without any impact on customers or service delivery</p><p> </p><p>DWP does not receive any revenue from 0345 telephone lines.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2017-10-23T11:18:14.197Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/770080/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/770080/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/770080/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-10-13","Department for Work and Pensions: Telephone Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many 0345 telephone numbers are in use by his Department; and how much revenue has been generated by each such telephone number in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Jim McMahon","Oldham West and Royton","Jim McMahon","107738"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/770081","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-10-18","<p>The Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy (BEIS) has two 0345 numbers in operation: 0345 015 0010 which is the BEIS publications order line and 0345 001 2222 which is an Internal IT Service Desk helpline. No revenue is generated for either number.</p><p> </p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2017-10-18T14:16:55.917Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/770081/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/770081/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/770081/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-10-13","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy: Telephone Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, how many 0345 telephone numbers are in use by his Department; and how much revenue has been generated by each such telephone number in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Jim McMahon","Oldham West and Royton","Jim McMahon","107732"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/770082","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-10-18","<p>No 0345 telephone numbers have been used by the Foreign and Commonwealth Office since 2010.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2017-10-18T15:57:32.8Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/770082/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/770082/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/770082/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-10-13","Foreign and Commonwealth Office: Telephone Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, how many 0345 telephone numbers are in use by his Department; and how much revenue has been generated by each telephone number in each such year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Jim McMahon","Oldham West and Royton","Jim McMahon","107733"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/770083","Department of Health","false","2017-10-18","<p>The Department does not use premium rate telephones lines where any accruals are made by the Department, and has not done so over the past five years.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2017-10-18T11:39:45.12Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/770083/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/770083/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/770083/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-10-13","Department of Health: Telephone Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many 0345 telephone numbers are in use by his Department; and how much revenue has been generated by each such telephone number in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Jim McMahon","Oldham West and Royton","Jim McMahon","107734"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/770084","Home Office","false","2017-10-20","<p>The Home Office has one 0345 telephone number in use. The number came into effect in 2014 and no revenue has been generated by this number since its introduction.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2017-10-20T09:37:14.037Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/770084/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/770084/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/770084/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-10-13","Home Office: Telephone Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many 0345 telephone numbers are in use by her Department; and how much revenue has been generated by each such telephone number in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Jim McMahon","Oldham West and Royton","Jim McMahon","107735"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/770085","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-10-23","<p>The MoJ does not have a central repository of this information as the disparate sites and cost centres i.e CRCs, ALBs, are empowered to order services such as these independently. Whilst there may be some 0345 numbers in existence, it should be noted that they are NOT revenue generating numbers. These numbers can actually result in a cost to the MoJ, depending upon their usage and provider conditions.</p><p> </p><p>0345 numbers usually cost no more than a standard landline. The exact amount depends on their provider and may even be “free” i.e. included in their package.</p>","Bracknell","Dr Phillip Lee",,"2017-10-23T16:56:42.843Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/770085/answer","Biography information for Dr Phillip Lee","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/770085/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/770085/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-10-13","Ministry of Justice: Telephone Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many 0345 telephone numbers are in use by his Department; and how much revenue has been generated by each such telephone number in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Jim McMahon","Oldham West and Royton","Jim McMahon","107736"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/770086","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-10-23","<p>It is not Government’s policy to publish documents of this nature.</p><p> </p><p>The Universal Credit programme is already subject to a robust regime of internal and external scrutiny, including oversight from the Work and Pensions Select Committee, the Public Accounts Committee, the National Audit Office and the Infrastructure and Projects Authority.</p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2017-10-23T16:58:07.467Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/770086/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/770086/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/770086/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-10-13","Universal Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, if it will publish the risk register for the roll-out of universal credit.","false","Biography information for Jim McMahon","Oldham West and Royton","Jim McMahon","107692"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/770087","Department for Education","false","2017-10-25","<p>As part of Ofsted school inspections, inspectors consider how well leaders and governors promote all forms of equality and how well the school prepares pupils positively for life in modern Britain.</p><p>In April 2016, Her Majesty's Chief Inspector of Education, Children’s Services and Skills wrote to my Rt hon. Friend, the Secretary of State, making clear that where inspectors identify any form of segregation in a mixed school, without a good educational reason, this would likely lead to an inadequate judgement for the school’s leadership and management. This is consistent with the Department’s longstanding position that mixed schools should only separate children by gender in limited circumstances where this can be justified and where they can demonstrate that no pupil is disadvantaged by virtue of their gender.</p><p>The recent case of Her Majesty's Chief Inspector of Education, Children’s Services and Skills –v- The Interim Executive Board of Al-Hijrah School has clarified the law in a way which supports that position.</p><p>It will be for any other schools affected by the judgment to decide what action they might need to take in the light of the judgment. The Department will work with any affected schools to help them comply with the law.<strong><br> </strong></p>","Guildford","Anne Milton",,"2017-10-25T16:19:48.977Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/770087/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/770087/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/770087/answer","Guildford","Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/770087/answer/previousversion/16029","Biography information for Anne Milton","60","Education","Education","2017-10-13","Schools: Discrimination","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, whether her Department monitors particular schools for gender segregation.","false","Biography information for Jim McMahon","Oldham West and Royton","Jim McMahon","107715"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/770088","Cabinet Office","false","2017-10-18","<p>The cost to the public purse of the Boundary Commission for England’s 2018 Review to date is £3.3 million.</p>","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore",,"2017-10-18T09:58:55.04Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/770088/answer","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/770088/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/770088/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-10-13","Constituencies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what the total cost to the public purse to date is of the Boundary Commission for England's 2018 Review.","false","Biography information for Jim McMahon","Oldham West and Royton","Jim McMahon","107681"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/770089","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-10-18","<p>HMCTS currently has a contract with a number of Approved Enforcement Agencies (AEAs) for the execution of criminal warrants and orders and this includes the warrants of control. The table below is the information recorded for the current contract which commenced in December 2009. This data is restricted to warrants of control relating to criminal cases only. These warrants are normally issued when all other sanctions have failed and AEAs are only paid on successful execution. All returned warrants are reviewed to consider alternative method of enforcement. The contract measure is for the number of warrants fully paid within 180 days of issue, shown in column three. Other payments will be made outside the 180 days but we do not have performance data on them.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td colspan="5"><p>Approved Enforcement Agency Contract -Warrants of Control</p></td></tr><tr><td><p> </p></td><td rowspan="2"><p><strong>Issued</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Number Fully Paid</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Executed </strong></p></td><td rowspan="2"><p><strong>Total Cash received per annum</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p> </p></td><td colspan="2"><p><strong>in 180 days</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2009/10</strong></p></td><td><p>553,726</p></td><td><p>92,906</p></td><td><p>18.67%</p></td><td><p>£21,436,700</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2010/11</strong></p></td><td><p>564,116</p></td><td><p>101,303</p></td><td><p>19.63%</p></td><td><p>£22,642,734</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2011/12</strong></p></td><td><p>652,427</p></td><td><p>138,036</p></td><td><p>23.59%</p></td><td><p>£30,480,254</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2012/13</strong></p></td><td><p>675,431</p></td><td><p>131,215</p></td><td><p>22.37%</p></td><td><p>£31,143,255</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2013/14</strong></p></td><td><p>647,642</p></td><td><p>125,020</p></td><td><p>23.10%</p></td><td><p>£38,893,841</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2014/15</strong></p></td><td><p>736,663</p></td><td><p>149,437</p></td><td><p>24.98%</p></td><td><p>£47,816,967</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2015/16</strong></p></td><td><p>598,224</p></td><td><p>127,578</p></td><td><p>26.26%</p></td><td><p>£44,207,156</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2016/17</strong></p></td><td><p>590,649</p></td><td><p>133,850</p></td><td><p>26.68%</p></td><td><p>£55,003,836</p></td></tr></tbody></table>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab",,"2017-10-18T14:21:36.59Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/770089/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/770089/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/770089/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-10-13","Debt Collection","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what the collection rates were for warrants of control by HM Courts and Tribunals Service on Warrants of Control for each year since 2008.","false","Biography information for Rachel Maclean","Redditch","Rachel Maclean","107727"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/770090","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-10-18","<p>The table below illustrates the total numbers of arrest warrants issued to HMCTS Civilian Enforcement Officers, the police and the Approved Enforcement Agencies to be executed during each of the last three years.</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong> </strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2016/2017</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2015/2016</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2014/2015</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Financial arrest</p></td><td><p>145,373</p></td><td><p>207,322</p></td><td><p>213,773</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Community Penalty Breach Warrant</p></td><td><p>20,266</p></td><td><p>16,736</p></td><td><p>17,317</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Total</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>165,639</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>224,058</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>231,090</strong></p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>It is not possible to identify and calculate how many of these warrants of arrest were specifically executed by civilian enforcement officers in any specific year without incurring disproportionate costs.</p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab",,"2017-10-18T14:20:50.027Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/770090/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/770090/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/770090/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-10-13","Arrest Warrants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many warrants of arrest have been (a) issued by HM Courts and Tribunals Service and (b) executed by civilian enforcement officers in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Rachel Maclean","Redditch","Rachel Maclean","107712"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/770091","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-10-18","<p>The information requested is not readily available and to provide it would incur disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p><p>We have recently published the following statistics on the number of people who have had Access to Work provision approved: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/access-to-work-statistics" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/access-to-work-statistics</a>.</p><p> </p><p>These statistics have been developed using guidelines set out by the UK Statistics Authority and are new official statistics undergoing development. They have therefore been designated as experimental statistics. We plan to publish these statistics on an annual basis and will explore the feasibility of expanding their scope to cover other parts of the Access to Work customer journey such as Access to Work payments. Users are invited to comment on the development and relevance of these statistics at this stage and can send feedback to: <a href="mailto:access.toworkstatistics@dwp.gsi.gov.uk" target="_blank">access.toworkstatistics@dwp.gsi.gov.uk</a>. Your questions above will also be considered as part of the development of the statistics.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt","107706 ; 107707 ; 107717","2017-10-18T09:50:25.727Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/770091/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/770091/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/770091/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-10-13","Access to Work Programme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many Access to Work reassessments have been conducted in each year since 2009-10.","false","Biography information for Debbie Abrahams","Oldham East and Saddleworth","Debbie Abrahams","107705"
