"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769769","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-10-17","<p>The Department has undertaken an Equality Assessment on the proposal to cap housing benefit at the Local Housing Allowance rates for people in supported housing.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2017-10-17T09:31:31.67Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769769/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769769/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769769/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-10-12","Housing Benefit: Supported Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what plans he has to undertake an equalities impact assessment of the proposed cap on housing benefit for those in supported housing.","false","Biography information for Melanie Onn","Great Grimsby","Melanie Onn","107328"
