"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769787","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-10-24","<p>The Government is working to deliver the best international trading framework for the UK. We are working with other Departments to assess the full range of options for a future tariff regime that will best serve the interests of UK consumers, businesses and farmers. The evidence available will be considered carefully before a final decision is made.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2017-10-24T11:27:15.377Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769787/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769787/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769787/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-10-12","Manufactured Goods: Import Duties","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, whether his Department has made an assessment of the effect on UK manufacturing of the UK unilaterally removing all import tariffs after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Matthew Pennycook","Greenwich and Woolwich","Matthew Pennycook","107379"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769788","Department for Transport","false","2017-10-19","<p>The Government and the Civil Aviation Authority (CAA) are taking a number of steps to increase the public’s awareness of ATOL protection. Consumers can find information about ATOL and the products and companies that are covered on the CAA’s website. CAA have also launched the <em>‘Pack Peace of Mind’</em> campaign to increase awareness of ATOL protection.</p><p> </p><p>We are also taking steps to ensure consumers are informed about ATOL protection when they book a holiday. Companies that sell ATOL protected holidays are already required to provide an ATOL certificate to consumers when they purchase a protected trip or flight. We will introduce additional pre and post-sale information requirements when we implement a new EU Package Travel Directive in 2018.</p><p> </p><p>The Government is continuing to keep this under review as we develop a new aviation strategy for the UK. In July 2017 we published a call for evidence on the aviation strategy, which invited views on whether further information provisions and consumer protections are needed in the sector. We will cover these issues in more detail in the next stage of the consultation.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2017-10-19T10:05:03.013Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769788/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769788/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769788/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-10-12","ATOL","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what steps the Government is taking to increase public awareness of the extent of the protection extended to commercial flights by ATOL.","false","Biography information for Daniel Kawczynski","Shrewsbury and Atcham","Daniel Kawczynski","107385"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769789","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-10-18","<p>Remuneration policies of quoted companies must be put to a binding shareholder vote at least once every three years. A binding shareholder vote is required to approve any Directors’ remuneration that falls outside the scope of the approved remuneration policy.</p><p>The annual Directors Remuneration Report on implementation of the remuneration policy is subject to an advisory shareholder vote. If this vote is lost, a company must put a new remuneration policy to a binding shareholder vote within twelve months.</p><p>The Government has no current plans to change these existing shareholder voting provisions.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2017-10-18T14:37:51.44Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769789/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769789/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769789/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-10-12","Managers: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what the Government's policy is on executive pay being approved by an annual vote of shareholders.","false","Biography information for Emma Reynolds","Wolverhampton North East","Emma Reynolds","107482"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769790","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-10-18","<p>The Government’s response to the Corporate Governance Reform green paper consultation invited The Investment Association to implement its proposal to establish a public register of quoted companies encountering shareholder opposition of 20% or more to executive pay and other resolutions. The Investment Association is working to establish the register by the end of the year and the number of companies included will be confirmed at that time.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2017-10-18T14:38:14.877Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769790/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769790/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769790/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-10-12","Managers: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, when the Government plans to introduce the register on shareholder voting announced by the Prime Minister on 27 August 2017; and whether his Department has undertaken an impact assessment of the number of companies it expects to be placed on that register.","false","Biography information for Emma Reynolds","Wolverhampton North East","Emma Reynolds","107435"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769792","Department for International Trade","false","2017-10-20","<p>My Rt Hon Friend the Secretary of State for International Trade, regularly discusses trade policy issues with Cabinet colleagues, including my Rt Hon Friend the Home Secretary. This includes looking at how UK domestic policies can support the UK’s trade agenda.</p><p> </p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2017-10-20T11:49:12.547Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769792/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769792/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769792/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-10-12","Trade Agreements: Immigration Controls","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, what discussions he has had with Cabinet colleagues on lowering the UK's visa restrictions in the context of negotiating future trade deals with other countries.","false","Biography information for Damien Moore","Southport","Damien Moore","107384"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769793","Department for International Trade","false","2017-10-18","<p>The Department for International Trade has a strong and capable trade policy team which has grown significantly since its establishment in July 2016 and is continuing to grow.</p><p>We continue to hire the brightest and best talent from within the UK civil service and externally, in order to build a world class trade policy team that can deliver the best outcomes for the UK.</p><p>Internationally recognised expert Crawford Falconer is now in post as DIT’s Chief Trade Negotiation Adviser and Second Permanent Secretary.</p><p>Mr Falconer will support the establishment of a world-class trade negotiation function and lead the development of the International Trade profession for trade negotiators. He has <br>more than 25 years of public service experience in trade and foreign affairs.</p><p /><p />","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2017-10-18T16:24:53.817Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769793/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769793/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769793/answer","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769793/answer/previousversion/15708","Biography information for Greg Hands","202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-10-12","Department for International Trade: Trade Agreements","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, how many officials employed in his Department as of 12 October 2017 have substantial experience of international trade negotiations.","false","Biography information for Kirsty Blackman","Aberdeen North","Kirsty Blackman","107364"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769794","Department for International Trade","false","2017-10-18","<p>I refer the hon Member to the answer I gave her today, UIN: 107364.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2017-10-18T16:33:57.003Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769794/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769794/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769794/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-10-12","Department for International Trade: Trade Agreements","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, how many officials employed in his Department in June 2016 had substantial experience of international trade negotiation.","false","Biography information for Kirsty Blackman","Aberdeen North","Kirsty Blackman","107344"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769795","Department for International Trade","false","2017-10-20","<p>The Department for International Trade (DIT) runs nearly 200 export High Value Campaigns, across a range of countries, the majority being non-EU, focusing government resources where they add the most value for the benefit of the whole of the UK. Since the election in June, DIT has been reviewing its exports strategy which partners across the world working closely with the FCO and DfID to look beyond traditional markets to support wider government objectives.</p>","Wyre Forest","Mark Garnier",,"2017-10-20T13:39:22.823Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769795/answer","Biography information for Mark Garnier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769795/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769795/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-10-12","Exports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, what assessment he has made of export opportunities for the UK in non-EU countries.","false","Biography information for Mr Peter Bone","Wellingborough","Mr Peter Bone","107310"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769796","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-10-17","<p>The Department for Exiting the European Union has released information on the UK's negotiating team which is publicly available on<a href="http://gov.uk/" target="_blank"> gov.uk</a>. The information requested is not held centrally and therefore, we are not in a position to provide this for particular groups of staff.</p><p>The Department for Exiting the European Union now has over 500 staff and is drawing together expertise from a wide range of departments where there is specific and relevant knowledge. All departments are equipping themselves with the resources they need to get the best deal for the UK.</p><p> </p>","Wycombe","Mr Steve Baker","107342","2017-10-17T11:57:36.95Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769796/answer","Biography information for Mr Steve Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769796/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769796/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-10-12","Department for Exiting the European Union: Trade Agreements","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, how many officials employed in his Department as of 12 October 2017 have substantial experience of international trade negotiations.","false","Biography information for Kirsty Blackman","Aberdeen North","Kirsty Blackman","107362"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769797","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-10-17","<p>The Department for Exiting the European Union has released information on the UK's negotiating team which is publicly available on<a href="http://gov.uk/" target="_blank"> gov.uk</a>. The information requested is not held centrally and therefore, we are not in a position to provide this for particular groups of staff.</p><p>The Department for Exiting the European Union now has over 500 staff and is drawing together expertise from a wide range of departments where there is specific and relevant knowledge. All departments are equipping themselves with the resources they need to get the best deal for the UK.</p><p> </p>","Wycombe","Mr Steve Baker","107362","2017-10-17T11:57:36.997Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769797/answer","Biography information for Mr Steve Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769797/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769797/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-10-12","Department for Exiting the European Union: Trade Agreements","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, how many officials employed in his Department in June 2016 had substantial experience of international trade negotiation.","false","Biography information for Kirsty Blackman","Aberdeen North","Kirsty Blackman","107342"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769798","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-10-20","<p>The information requested is not held centrally and therefore, we are not in a position to provide this for particular groups of staff.<br><br>The Department for Exiting the European Union now has over 500 staff and is drawing together expertise from a wide range of departments where there is specific relevant knowledge. All departments are equipping themselves with the resources they need to get the best deal for the UK.</p>","Wycombe","Mr Steve Baker",,"2017-10-20T11:52:04.683Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769798/answer","Biography information for Mr Steve Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769798/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769798/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-10-12","Department for Exiting the European Union: Health","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, how many officials of his Department have expertise in health.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","107378"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769799","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-10-20","<p>Throughout the process of the negotiations we have sought to understand the unique challenges of our UK nationals already living in the EU. Ministers from the Department for Exiting the European Union have met delegates from groups representing UK nationals in the EU, to hear their views and concerns. Our Embassies and Ambassadors in the remaining EU27 have also engaged extensively with their communities in country. As negotiations progress we will continue to work in the interests of our nationals, and we remain confident that we will be able to reach the best possible reciprocal deal to secure their rights.</p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker",,"2017-10-20T13:11:00.47Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769799/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769799/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769799/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-10-12","Brexit: British Nationals Abroad","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, what steps he is taking to ensure that the views of UK citizens living in the EU are taken into account during the negotiations on the UK leaving the EU.","false","Biography information for Kate Green","Stretford and Urmston","Kate Green","107443"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769800","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-10-20","<p>We are taking a cross-Whitehall approach to engagement and working closely with the Department for Digital, Culture, Media &amp; Sport to ensure that we speak to stakeholders who represent a range of groups and opinions. The Government continues to listen to the voices of young people as negotiations progress. Ministers and officials from the Department for Exiting the EU have worked with colleagues across Government and held bilateral meetings and a number of roundtables with youth organisations that represent a cross-section of young people.</p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker","107441","2017-10-20T13:59:34.337Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769800/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769800/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769800/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-10-12","Brexit: Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, what steps he is taking to ensure that the views of children and young people are taken into account during the negotiations on the UK leaving the EU.","false","Biography information for Kate Green","Stretford and Urmston","Kate Green","107442"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769801","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-10-20","<p>We are taking a cross-Whitehall approach to engagement and working closely with the Department for Digital, Culture, Media &amp; Sport to ensure that we speak to stakeholders who represent a range of groups and opinions. The Government continues to listen to the voices of young people as negotiations progress. Ministers and officials from the Department for Exiting the EU have worked with colleagues across Government and held bilateral meetings and a number of roundtables with youth organisations that represent a cross-section of young people.</p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker","107442","2017-10-20T13:59:34.287Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769801/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769801/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769801/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-10-12","Brexit: Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, what steps he is taking to ensure that young people who were unable to vote in the 2016 EU referendum are being taken into account during the negotiations on the UK leaving the EU.","false","Biography information for Kate Green","Stretford and Urmston","Kate Green","107441"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769802","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-10-17","<p>The Government is committed to negotiating a deep and special partnership with the European Union and is conducting a wide-ranging programme of analysis. It would not be appropriate, however, to publish details that could undermine the UK's negotiating position with the EU, and Parliament has voted not to publish such details.</p>","Wycombe","Mr Steve Baker",,"2017-10-17T14:35:26.123Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769802/answer","Biography information for Mr Steve Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769802/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769802/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-10-12","Economic Situation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, pursuant to the Answer of 13 September 2017 to Question 8561, if he will publish his Department's studies into the effect of the UK leaving the EU on different sectors of the UK economy.","false","Biography information for Mr David Lammy","Tottenham","Mr David Lammy","107481"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769803","Attorney General","false","2017-10-17","<p>The CPS regularly consults with Muslim community based organisations to address anti-Muslim prejudice and hate crime. Nationally, the CPS consults with community-based organisations through its Community Accountability Forum, which includes a representative from the All Parliamentary Group on British Muslims. At a local level, Inclusion and Community Engagement Managers also engage with local Muslim community based organisations through Local Scrutiny and Involvement Panels (LSIPs) in each CPS Area.</p><p>The CPS circulated the job advert containing details of the posts of Inclusion and Community Engagement Managers to the Community Accountability Forum, LSIPs and other community contacts, to encourage the widest possible pool of people to apply.</p><p>The CPS is also a member of the cross Government anti-Muslim Hatred Working Group, the cross Government Hate Crime Strategic Group, and the Independent Advisory Group on Hate Crime, all of which include a number of representatives from Muslim organisations that actively tackle anti-Muslim hatred.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Kenilworth and Southam","Jeremy Wright",,"2017-10-17T15:17:23.527Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769803/answer","Biography information for Jeremy Wright","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769803/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769803/answer",,,,,"88","Attorney General","Attorney General","2017-10-12","Religious Hatred: Islam","1","House of Commons","To ask the Attorney General, with reference to page 11 of the Crown Prosecution Service's (CPS) 2016-17 annual report, on the appointment of inclusion and community engagement managers, whether the CPS consulted (a) Muslim community based organisations and (b) other groups addressing anti-Muslim prejudice and hate crime.","false","Biography information for Afzal Khan","Manchester, Gorton","Afzal Khan","107504"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769804","Cabinet Office","false","2017-10-17","<p><strong>The Shadow Government Property Agency (GPA) is committed to delivering transformational change across government departments including hubs, IT and smarter working. To achieve this, the GPA continues to work closely with government departments to understand requirements in readiness for the robust delivery of property services and benefits to government. </strong></p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2017-10-17T13:51:24.517Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769804/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769804/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769804/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-10-12","Government Departments: Buildings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, pursuant to the Answers of 12 October 2017 to Question 105513 and of 12 September 2017 to Question 8360, what the reasons are for the time taken to launch the Government Property Agency; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","107644"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769805","Cabinet Office","false","2017-11-28","<p>The Intelligence and Security Committee has been appointed following the approval of motions in both Houses of Parliament.</p>","Ashford","Damian Green",,"2017-11-28T15:48:28.157Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769805/answer","Biography information for Damian Green","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769805/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769805/answer","Ashford","Damian Green","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769805/answer/previousversion/15343","Biography information for Damian Green","53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-10-12","Intelligence and Security Committee","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, when he expects the Intelligence Security Committee for the current Parliament to be formally reconstituted; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","107524"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769806","Cabinet Office","false","2017-10-23","<p><strong>It is normal practice to review the release of specific information that may risk the identification of individual employees. In my Department, information that involves five or fewer individuals is the threshold at which its release is reviewed. As the individual involved is not senior staff in my Department, we respectfully decline this request for more detailed information</strong></p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2017-10-23T13:00:47.173Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769806/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769806/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769806/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-10-12","Government Property Unit: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, pursuant to the Answer of 12 October to Question 105943, from which organisation that member of staff has been seconded from; and for what time period that staff member has been seconded.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","107495"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769807","HM Treasury","false","2017-10-20","<p>The Border Planning Group was formally established with its inaugural meeting on 29 March 2017.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2017-10-20T12:00:09.227Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769807/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769807/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769807/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-10-12","Border Planning Group","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, when the HM Revenue and Customs Border Planning Group was established.","false","Biography information for Charlie Elphicke","Dover","Charlie Elphicke","107593"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769808","HM Treasury","false","2017-10-20","<p>The Border Planning Group was formally established with its inaugural meeting on 29 March 2017.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2017-10-20T11:55:56.833Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769808/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769808/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769808/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-10-12","Border Planning Group","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, when the HM Revenue and Customs Border Planning Group held its first meeting.","false","Biography information for Charlie Elphicke","Dover","Charlie Elphicke","107594"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769809","HM Treasury","false","2017-10-20","<p>The Border Planning Group is a cross-Whitehall group of senior officials set up by Permanent Secretaries. It is chaired by Permanent Secretaries and includes senior level (Director General and Director level) civil servants from all relevant Departments with responsibility for border related activities or policy.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2017-10-20T11:58:35.143Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769809/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769809/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769809/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-10-12","Border Planning Group","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, who the current members of the HM Revenue and Customs Border Planning Group are.","false","Biography information for Charlie Elphicke","Dover","Charlie Elphicke","107595"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769810","HM Treasury","false","2017-10-20","<p>The Border Planning Group has met six times since being established. The Group plans to meet on a monthly basis.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2017-10-20T11:58:04.11Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769810/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769810/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769810/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-10-12","Border Planning Group","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, when the HM Revenue and Customs Border Planning Group has (a) met on what dates and (b) plans to meet.","false","Biography information for Charlie Elphicke","Dover","Charlie Elphicke","107598"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769811","HM Treasury","false","2017-10-20","<p>Surge and Rapid Response Team staff conduct a restricted role compared to Border Force Officers. They work at primary control points checking passports. Surge and Rapid Response Team staff undertake the same training programme and proficiency test procedures as all Border Force seasonal workers.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2017-10-20T12:07:32.15Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769811/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769811/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769811/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-10-12","Revenue and Customs: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, pursuant to the Answer of 20 July 2017 to Question 4611, whether Surge and Rapid Response Team staff receive training to the same standard as the Border Force staff they work alongside.","false","Biography information for Chris Stephens","Glasgow South West","Chris Stephens","107498"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769812","HM Treasury","false","2017-10-20","<p>The Border Planning Group’s next meeting is scheduled for 11 November 2017</p><p> </p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2017-10-20T11:52:59.177Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769812/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769812/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769812/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-10-12","Border Planning Group","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, when the next meeting of the HM Revenue and Customs Border Planning Group will take place.","false","Biography information for Charlie Elphicke","Dover","Charlie Elphicke","107599"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769813","HM Treasury","false","2017-10-20","With any deployment undertaken by the Surge and Rapid Response Team (SRRT), HM Revenue and Customs charge the full direct cost including VAT. Any Travel and Subsistence costs incurred on the deployment are also re-charged.","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2017-10-20T11:59:50.943Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769813/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769813/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769813/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-10-12","Revenue and Customs: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, pursuant to the Answer of 20 July 2017 to Question 4611, whether HM Revenue and Customs charges Border Force the full cost, including VAT, for the provision of staff providing assistance.","false","Biography information for Chris Stephens","Glasgow South West","Chris Stephens","107499"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769814","HM Treasury","false","2017-10-20","<p>The Border Planning Group is a cross-Whitehall group of senior officials set up by Permanent Secretaries. The role of the Border Planning Group is to provide oversight of and assurance of departmental planning for border related issues arising from leaving the EU. The Border Coordination Team within HMRC supports the work of the Border Planning Group and reports into it. The budget for this team for 2017-18 is £2.5m. There are a large number of different teams across Government departments (including other teams in HMRC) working on border related EU exit matters for which funding will be within individual departmental budgets.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2017-10-20T11:56:47Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769814/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769814/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769814/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-10-12","Border Planning Group","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what annual budget has been allocated to the HM Revenue and Customs Border Planning Group.","false","Biography information for Charlie Elphicke","Dover","Charlie Elphicke","107596"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769815","HM Treasury","false","2017-10-20","<p>The Border Planning Group is a cross-Whitehall group of senior officials set up by Permanent Secretaries. The Border Planning Group’s role is to provide oversight and assurance of departmental plans for border related impacts of leaving the EU. The Border Planning Group does not report to the Chancellor and it has not contributed directly to the Autumn Budget 2017. Some individuals on it will have been involved in the Autumn Budget process.</p><p> </p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2017-10-20T11:51:18.023Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769815/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769815/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769815/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-10-12","Border Planning Group","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what contribution the HM Revenue and Customs Border Planning Group has made to the Autumn Budget 2017.","false","Biography information for Charlie Elphicke","Dover","Charlie Elphicke","107597"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769816","HM Treasury","false","2017-10-20","<p>The Border Planning Group’s minutes will not be released as these relate to the formulation or development of government policy.</p><p> </p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2017-10-20T11:55:06.443Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769816/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769816/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769816/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-10-12","Border Planning Group","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will place in the Library a copy of the minutes of the HM Revenue and Customs Border Planning Group meetings.","false","Biography information for Charlie Elphicke","Dover","Charlie Elphicke","107583"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769817","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-10-20","<p>The Pensions Regulator (TPR) has the power to appoint an independent trustee in certain circumstances where it is necessary and appropriate to do so. TPR is the independent regulator for workplace pensions and, as such, it would not be appropriate for me to comment in more detail.</p>","Hexham","Guy Opperman",,"2017-10-20T10:46:19.337Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769817/answer","Biography information for Guy Opperman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769817/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769817/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-10-12","Pension Funds: QG Apollo Limited","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what the timetable is for the Pension Regulator to appoint a trustee to manage the QG Apollo Pension Scheme.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","107458"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769818","HM Treasury","false","2017-10-18","<p>The Government has undertaken a significant amount of work to assess the economic impacts of leaving the EU. This is part of our continued programme of analytical work on a range of scenarios on a sector by sector basis.</p><p> </p><p>We are seeking the best deal possible and the work being done reflects this.</p><p> </p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay",,"2017-10-18T13:43:03.877Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769818/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769818/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769818/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-10-12","Economic Situation","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether his Department has reviewed the economic modelling that underpinned his Department's paper, The long-term economic impact of EU membership and the alternatives, published on 18 April 2016; and what the conclusions were of that review.","false","Biography information for Matthew Pennycook","Greenwich and Woolwich","Matthew Pennycook","107633"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769819","HM Treasury","false","2017-10-20","<p>Since April 2016, 1,824 staff have started their apprenticeships in HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) either through being recruited as apprentices or by existing staff taking up an apprenticeship. Apprenticeship starts by nation is as follows:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Nation</p></td><td><p>Apprenticeship starts</p></td><td><p>% of apprenticeship starts</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>England</p></td><td><p>1,304</p></td><td><p>71%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Scotland</p></td><td><p>243</p></td><td><p>13%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Wales</p></td><td><p>275</p></td><td><p>15%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Northern Ireland</p></td><td><p>2</p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Total</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>1,824</strong></p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p>As an employer with a pay bill in excess of £3m pa, HMRC pays 0.5% of its pay bill into the apprenticeship levy on a monthly basis.</p><p> </p><p>This equates to monthly payments of:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Month</p></td><td><p>Apr 17</p></td><td><p>May 17</p></td><td><p>Jun 17</p></td><td><p>Jul 17</p></td><td><p>Aug 17</p></td><td><p>Sept 17</p></td><td><p>Total</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>£’000s</p></td><td><p>N/A</p></td><td><p>743</p></td><td><p>747</p></td><td><p>748</p></td><td><p>794</p></td><td><p>748</p></td><td><p>3,780</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p>The digital apprenticeship service account went live in May 2017. It is the responsibility of the learning providers to draw down funding from the Digital Account. HMRC has been working with providers and the first payments have been made in October.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Month</p></td><td><p>Apr 17</p></td><td><p>May 17</p></td><td><p>Jun 17</p></td><td><p>Jul 17</p></td><td><p>Aug 17</p></td><td><p>Sept 17</p></td><td><p>Oct 17</p></td><td><p>Total</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>£</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td>