"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769824","HM Treasury","false","2017-10-20","<p>In line with the requirements of the Civil Service Management Code, an employee subject to formal warnings under the attendance management policy has a right of appeal at each formal decision point of the attendance management process. The HMRC appeals procedure is available to all employees via their intranet and clearly sets out the process and route via an impartial appeal manager.</p><p> </p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2017-10-20T12:08:27.383Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769824/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769824/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769824/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-10-12","Revenue and Customs: Disciplinary Proceedings","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, with reference to page 113 of the HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) Annual Report and Accounts 2016-17, whether staff subject to formal warnings under the attendance management policy submit and progress appeals in accordance with the provisions set out in paragraph 4.515 of the Civil Service Management Code.","false","Biography information for Chris Stephens","Glasgow South West","Chris Stephens","107639"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769825","HM Treasury","false","2017-10-20","The number of HMRC employees that are non-UK EEA nationals broken down by grade is given in the table below<p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>AA</p></td><td><p>AO</p></td><td><p>O</p></td><td><p>HO</p></td><td><p>Band T</p></td><td><p>SO</p></td><td><p>G7</p></td><td><p>G6</p></td><td><p>SCS</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2</p></td><td><p>246</p></td><td><p>118</p></td><td><p>82</p></td><td><p>19</p></td><td><p>32</p></td><td><p>42</p></td><td><p>8</p></td><td><p>2</p></td></tr></tbody></table>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2017-10-20T11:57:27.553Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769825/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769825/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769825/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-10-12","Revenue and Customs: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many employees of HM Revenue and Customs are non-UK EEA nationals in each pay grade.","false","Biography information for Chris Stephens","Glasgow South West","Chris Stephens","107472"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769826","HM Treasury","false","2017-10-20","<p>The average cost of a standard referral for occupational health advice in HMRC is £55.63</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2017-10-20T12:05:41.363Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769826/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769826/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769826/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-10-12","Revenue and Customs: Sick Leave","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, pursuant to the Answer of 23 July 2017 to Question 5903, what the average cost to the public purse of a referral for occupational health advice is.","false","Biography information for Chris Stephens","Glasgow South West","Chris Stephens","107471"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769827","HM Treasury","false","2017-10-20","<p>In line with the requirements of the ACAS Code of Practice on Disciplinary and Grievance Procedures, an employee subject to formal warnings under the attendance management policy has a right of appeal at each formal decision point of the attendance management process. The HMRC appeals procedure is available to all employees via the HMRC intranet and clearly sets out the process and route via an impartial appeal manager.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2017-10-20T11:55:01.467Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769827/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769827/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769827/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-10-12","Revenue and Customs: Disciplinary Proceedings","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, with reference to page 113 of the HM Revenue and Customs Annual Report and Accounts 2016-17, whether staff subject to formal warnings under the attendance management policy submit and progress appeals in accordance with the provisions set out in paragraphs 26 to 29 of the ACAS Code of Practice on Disciplinary and Grievance Procedures.","false","Biography information for Chris Stephens","Glasgow South West","Chris Stephens","107610"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769828","HM Treasury","false","2017-10-20","The programme aims to give participants an opportunity to increase their employability skills and gain office experience. Experience is gained through shadowing, coaching, and undertaking supervised activities alongside HMRC employees. These activities will vary dependent on the Business Area hosting the participant.","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2017-10-20T11:58:25.167Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769828/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769828/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769828/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-10-12","Revenue and Customs: Work Experience","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, with reference to page 112 of the HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) Annual Report and Accounts 2016-17, whether people on Movement to Work placements undertake work tasks that are also undertaken by employees of HMRC.","false","Biography information for Chris Stephens","Glasgow South West","Chris Stephens","107611"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769829","HM Treasury","false","2017-10-20","<p>HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) provides the Department for Education (DFE) with a ‘statement of account’ three times a year which give an estimate of total receipts DFE can expect at the end of the year based on repayments of student loans made via the tax system. DFE does not receive any borrower repayment information.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2017-10-20T12:06:44.717Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769829/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769829/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769829/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-10-12","Loans: Students","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, with reference to page 164 of the HM Revenue and Customs Annual Report and Accounts 2016-17, how frequently data on student loan recoveries made through the PAYE system using Real Time Information is passed to the Department for Education.","false","Biography information for Chris Stephens","Glasgow South West","Chris Stephens","107612"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769830","HM Treasury","false","2017-10-20","<p>The HMRC EU Nationals Network is sponsored by two HMRC directors who are actively engaged in supporting the Network objectives.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2017-10-20T12:06:55.66Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769830/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769830/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769830/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-10-12","Revenue and Customs: EU Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what support HM Revenue and Customs provides to the HMRC EU Nationals Network.","false","Biography information for Chris Stephens","Glasgow South West","Chris Stephens","107614"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769831","HM Treasury","false","2017-10-20","<p>HMRC ensures that its HR policies, procedures and practices are consistent with the regulations and conditions set out in the Civil Service Management Code.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride","108617","2017-10-20T12:11:58.553Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769831/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769831/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769831/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-10-12","Civil Servants: Codes of Practice","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what use HM Revenue and Customs makes of the Civil Service Management Code when formulating its personnel policy.","false","Biography information for Chris Stephens","Glasgow South West","Chris Stephens","107615"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769832","HM Treasury","false","2017-10-20","<p>HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) has a project underway looking at the business readiness for the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) which will be become law on 25 May 2018. It has appointed a Data Protection Officer, which is a mandatory position in public authorities, whose role is to advise HMRC on the actions necessary to ensure GDPR compliance, act as a first point of contact for regulators and for individuals whose data is processed.</p><p> </p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2017-10-20T11:47:38.39Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769832/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769832/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769832/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-10-12","Data Protection: EU Law","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what work is being undertaken by HM Revenue and Customs in respect of the General Data Protection Regulation.","false","Biography information for Chris Stephens","Glasgow South West","Chris Stephens","107616"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769833","HM Treasury","false","2017-10-20","<p>HMRC will follow the UK government policy on how to treat non-UK EEA national employees following the departure of the UK from the EU.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2017-10-20T11:56:10.263Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769833/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769833/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769833/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-10-12","Revenue and Customs: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether non-UK EEA nationals employed by HM Revenue and Customs will be subject to changes to their terms and conditions of employment after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Chris Stephens","Glasgow South West","Chris Stephens","107617"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769834","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-10-26","<p>My Department does not routinely record information pertaining to draft press releases.</p><p> </p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2017-10-26T13:58:57.77Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769834/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769834/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769834/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-10-12","Local Government: Press Releases","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, on how many occasions his Department has issued draft press releases to local authorities for them to complete using local statistics since May 2015.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","107621"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769835","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-10-17","<p>The Department wrote to all social landlords in November 2010 drawing their attention to guidance issued by the Chartered Institute of Housing designed to ensure tenants are provided with encouragement, help and advice on home working. The guidance, ‘Running a Business from Home’, includes advice for local authorities and other social landlords on how to amend their tenancies, if necessary, to make it easier for new and existing tenants to work from home</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2017-10-17T17:06:52.897Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769835/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769835/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769835/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-10-12","Social Rented Housing: Businesses","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what steps he has taken to remove barriers to social tenants running a business from home.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","107553"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769836","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-10-17","<p>The European Regional Development Fund (ERDF) 2014-2020 programme for England has been allocated to Local Enterprise Partnership areas (<a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/eu-structural-funds-uk-allocations-2014-to-2020" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/eu-structural-funds-uk-allocations-2014-to-2020</a>). The programme is valued at £2,830 million based on the current exchange rate.</p><p>Below is a breakdown of commitments by regional delivery team up to the end of June 2017.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong> Areas covered by ERDF Delivery Teams</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Commitments to end of June 2017 (£m)</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>London</p></td><td><p>51</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>East of England and South East</p></td><td><p>79</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>East and West Midlands</p></td><td><p>288</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>North East and Yorkshire &amp; the Humber</p></td><td><p>277</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>North West</p></td><td><p>248</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>South West</p></td><td><p>238</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Total</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>1,181</strong></p></td></tr></tbody></table>","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry",,"2017-10-17T11:24:52.193Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769836/answer","Biography information for Jake Berry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769836/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769836/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-10-12","European Regional Development Fund","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how much European Regional Development Fund funding by English region has been committed to projects to date; and what proportion of the total allocation that funding represents.","false","Biography information for 