"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769837","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-12-18","<p>The Government does not hold this information as local authorities were not required to report that they were compliant with the code. We are considering what further steps might be necessary to ensure compliance, given the Government’s desire to place more power and information into citizens’ hands so that democratic accountability is increased.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2017-12-18T13:47:47Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769837/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769837/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/769837/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-10-12","Local Government: Accountability","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, which local authorities were in breach of the local government transparency code in (a) 2015, (b) 2016 and (c) 2017 to date.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","107540"
